A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 19, 2025, as Nurses Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the more than 170,000 registered nurses in Georgia represent the state's largest
3 health care profession and are vital to the medical well-being of our citizens; and
4 WHEREAS, professional nursing has proven to be an indispensable component of the safe,
5 high quality care of hospitalized patients; and
6 WHEREAS, professional nurses are also vital to the outpatient care of patients, and the
7 renewed emphasis on access to primary and preventative care in recent years will require
8 better utilization of our state's registered nursing resources; and
9 WHEREAS, the aging of the American population, further reduction of health care options
10 in rural settings, and growth of home health care services have led to a greater than ever
11 demand for registered nursing services, and more qualified registered nurses will be needed
12 in the future to meet the increasingly complex needs of health care consumers in Georgia;
13 and
